The interviews and log at the end are very evocative but the description itself is very lackluster. The repetition of phrasing in “SCP-4254 will do this/as a result so will this” makes it feel very railroaded. I think not enough attention is given to the manifestation events, I think of you had these pieces of Elvis out here living lives in Las Vegas trailer parks living as impersonators it would lend them more depth. Instead they’re just narrative vehicles which ends up making the primary anomalous effect an almost superfluous part of its own article.








Whether you like it or not, history is on our side. We will bury you!






